>even if it was just stolen old ideas rebadged in some shiny new iPackage.
Anon, it's called '''being marketable'''. Just look at IBM. 108 year old company, "creator" of the personal computer, and they're not even worth a fraction of what Apple and Microsoft are worth (**In fact, the only reason they're still around is because of India buying all their tech**). Hell, Unix was available to the public for 8 years before MS-DOS came into the picture, followed by Mac OS, and, then, Windows; and the prevailing joke now is that the only people who use Unix (And it's forks) are hipsters and preppers. **And, this is ''ALSO'' leaving out that Plan 9, '''Unix's successor''', was left as a footnote in history due to the terrible marketing the thing was while Unix is still being actively developed to this very day.**

Before you someone says that this is in defense of all the actions these companies make, ==it is not.== The point I'm trying to make is that "being smart" doesn't a damn thing. A lot of smart people are dead broke, meanwhile "the idiots" who can sell people on a dream, on an idea, are living like kings. If people actually figured this out, instead of complaining about how people don't take the more progressive road that would make life so much better for them, perhaps things wouldn't be as terrible as they are.

posts.subject: The /pol/ Diet
posts.body:
Because of there being such conflicting information out there of what will and won't poison/kill you in regards to what you eat, I figured why not make a big thread discussing this so that we can know which substances are primarily beneficial, which are primarily harmful, and which don't make too much of a difference either way. And, there really needs to be a topic on this because, for example:
>Soy
Firsts, it's going to sterilize you and turn you into a woman: https://archive.fo/k8yja
Then, it isn't: https://archive.fo/0voxS
Then, soy is considered “healthy” if you ferment it or fry the crap out of it: https://archive.fo/mDoEP
''Or'', that soy is completely safe and it's the “greedy meat industry” who are spreading around the bad press: https://archive.fo/dUd3V
>MSG
You had articles coming out over a decade ago, that caused a big scare, about how MSG was going to kill you: https://archive.fo/eL687
Then, it comes into question why the Asians are not all dead: https://archive.fo/AqNE6
Then, it comes out that it was always “safe” for decades and the only reason it was hated was due to “racism”: https://archive.fo/Vvs8s
>Aspartame
First it's going to kill you: https://archive.ph/HMCII
Then it isn't: https://archive.ph/xxwIK
Then the entire source of the scare was a “Le Epic Troll of an old meme”: https://archive.ph/24eNo

You get the picture. So, what actions '''CAN''' we take to live long and healthy lives in regards to our food diets?
